Wish
This is the last mural I realized in Lecce, Italy for @167bstreet.

The mural is located in the 167B area, a huge multicultural and multiethnic social housing neighbourhood also known as the place where of one of the biggest Italian maxi trial against Mafia happened in the 90s.

Thanks to the 167bstreet organization the will of bringing beauty and improving the bonds between the inhabitants of the area is becoming reality.

My wall stands for this, for a connection that cannot be cut, a thin red line that links and ties all of us despite the difficulties, despite the twines, we definitely work better when we are not alone.

Photo Sergio Manzone.

Special thanks to @chekosart, Anjia and don Gerardo to have made it possible.

Tahitian Ibiscus

This is the  mural I realized for @onoutahiti in La Mission area in Papeete.

The goal of the project was to bring art in favor of social housing and all the the walls realized during this edition are located on social residencies for under privileged families of Tahiti.

Tahitian people are known worldwide for their gentle behaviour and hospitality and the island itself is an amazing and pure mix of nature, human environment and cultural heritage.
To be immersed in this unique scenario has been truly inspiring and allowed me to reflect also on how ephemeral could be the beauty of such this paradise on earth if we don't take care of it.

Tahitian people are so connected to nature that  all of their lives are based on it. 
Holding a flower could appear as a simple gesture but here I discovered that hides the pure respect towards every creations of mother nature,  and this is something that sometimes unfortunately we forget.

Special thanks to @selinamiles for the photos, and to @sarahroophinia  @oph_ polynesie  and their great team to have made it possible! MƒÅuruuru üôè

‚ÄúOpen‚Äù

I've realized this wall for the ‚ÄúAssociazione Volontari Campi Flegrei‚Äù in a neighborhood of Naples called Pianura.

The mural is on the facade of a temporary shelter built soon after the 1980's Irpinia earthquake and still inhabited. 
Before my arrival the facade was burnt by few parked cars on fire.
The association Volontari Campi Flegrei takes care in the afternoon, of the education of children and teenagers between 6 and 18 years old who live in particular conditions, with the goal of offering them a support in the study and an alternative to the "street life" in this west area of Naples.

During the last 6 months the children have worked on the theme of ‚Äúsensibility‚Äù and all its ramifications and I was choosen by them to realize this mural. ‚ÄúOpen‚Äù is an invitation to remain human towards each other and to let our feelings spread despite our cages.

Thank you to Chiara Fiorino and her family to have made it possible and to the #assaf√† whole team.

#millo #milloland #open #naples #napoli #pianura #volontariflegrei #mural #murals #streetart #urbanart #socialart #cage #goldencage

SHE LEANS AGAINST THE WIND

I've realized this mural for @milestoneproject in the beautiful city of Girona, Catalunya, Spain.

The wall is located in "Germans S√†bat" barrio, a small neighborhood built in the 50‚Äôs with the aim of hosting people coming from different regions of Spain in precarious conditions.
With the passing of time the "barrio", due to the growing of the city itself, turns to be a proper neighborhood of it.

The peculiarity of the "Barrio" is that it still keeps the original buildings and it's characterized by a strong collective feeling as a popoluation and a strong associational movement.

In this "barrio" I had the occasion to meet different people who all shared with me their stories, lives and memories.

I took my inspiration from them and from how something so connected to the tradition is still considered actual and  a beautiful and proud symbol of their folkrore and history.

Photos @aina_yraola

‚ÄúHandle with care‚Äù

This is the wall I realized for @sbaghabagha festival in Casablanca Morocco.

The wall is located in a big central area of the city dedicated to the wholesale trade. 
Everyday hundreds of trucks arrive ready to load and drop off goods. From the early morning till the dark thousands of boxes lie around the streets ready to leave or just arrived, it's a giant non stop open air market.
Handle with care seems to be the best advise I got, from all the people who were working there.
And at the same time "handle with care" is also an inviation  to be gentle with women that unfortunately are still struggling to be 100% recognized in the country.

#millo #milloland #morocco #casablanca #sbaghabagha #sbaghabagha19 #murals #streetart #streetartmorocco #art #publicart #box #handlewithcare #womanrights

Face the Ocean

I painted this wall in Carballo, Galicia, for @rexenerafest curated by @mutantecreativo .
Carballo is few km far from the seaside and for what is known as "Costa da morte" that spreads for 100km with its cliffs, reefs and lighthouses.

I found the inspiration in its beauty to express the importance of being sure of our inner strenght but also being ready to trust and rely on someone else.
In our sea journey we both could be the ship and the lighthouse in someone else's storm.

#rexenera #murals #costadamorte #lighthouse #millo #milloland

HOW TO

I painted this wall in Raiano, L'Aquila, for the first earthquake proof school realized in Abruzzo, Italy.

The theme behind the wall was the gender violence. In Italy over 100 women are killed every year and thousands of women pass through harrasments, violences and abuses.

That's why the decision to paint on a school wall. The students of this primary school chose between different drawings this sketch cause as they said, the simplicity of the image show the possibility to relate to genders with equality and kindness.¬†
Small acts can change an entire system.

Pics @iugin79 
#mural #murals #noviolence #noviolenceagainstwomen #howto #equality #kindness #children

HONGI - The breath of life.
@street_prints Manaia, Whangarei New Zeland

HONGI is the traditional MƒÅori greeting in New Zealand. It is done by pressing one's nose and forehead (at the same time) to another person.
During the hongi, the HA, or breath of life  is exchanged and intermingled. 
The breath of life is also considered the sharing of both parties' souls.

Hongi - The breath of life.
Whangarei, New Zealand.

HONGI is the traditional MƒÅori greeting in New Zealand. It is done by pressing one's nose and forehead (at the same time) to another person at an encounter.

During the hongi, the ‚Äúha‚Äù, or breath of life  is exchanged and intermingled. 
The breath of life is also considered the sharing of both parties' souls.

Through the exchange of this physical greeting, one is no longer considered "manuhiri" visitor, but rather "tangata whenua‚Äù, one of the people of the land.

#millo #milloland #hongi #staynative #streetprintmanaia #streetprint #manaia

This is the wall I realized in Dharavi , Mumbai for @startindia Foundation .

Dharavi is the biggest slum of Asia,
more than one million people in 1.7km2.
The living conditions are truly hard and the goal of the project is to bring art into the slum to make it known and more attractive for the inhabitants.

Dharavi is a unique place, with its colors, lights and loud sounds, it's where at least 5 different main religions lives together in armony, where the idea of "sharing" doesn't need to be thought cause it's reality, and where people smiles at you with all their soul.

In my imaginary under an umbrella blue as Indian nights able to protect from all the world ouside, through the mesmerized colors of the flowers, used to decorate anything in the neighborhood, my character dreams and moves towards a better future.

Pics @jaruskr (Suraj Ketra)
#millo#milloland #murals #mumbai #dharavi #startindia #startindiafoundation

‚ÄúRebirth‚Äù

I realized this work in Genk (Belgium) at Heempark for Lavazza 2019 calendar in partneship with United Nation Environment Programme.

Your will can make the difference, always.

During the last century Genk was known for his high concentration of coal mines where thousand of immigrants, especially Italians, went to work.
The living conditions for the workers and the citizens where critical, the level of air, soil and water pollution were at its maximum.
When in the 80s the government decided to close the mines Genk invested little by little in a sustainable development and started to convert the mines space into green places in order to increase the number of bees that were drastically reduced due to the pollution.

Now the city of Genk has 69 gardens where everybody can grow it's own organic food and help bees to spread in the area.

Moreover the entire project supports the Global Goals for Sustainable Dlevelpment.

#millo #milloland #genk #murales #mural #heempark #environment #pollutionfree

I've realized this wall in a kindergarten and primary school in Pescara for @par_pattoabruzzoresiliente 
The association goal is to inform as much as possible regarding the risks of our territory, and especially regarding the importance of having safe and functioning school structures.

Italy has been hitten by a series of natural events in this last dacade and much of them could have had a smaller impact if there were more informations and controls on cities structures.

Under a roof of culture and knowledge it's easier to think about a better future.

I've painted this multistory mural at the bus-train-boat station in Helsinborg ,Sweden for @kulturhotellet
I focused on three moments of travelling : when we dream about it, when we are ready to pack what we have just experienced and once back when we leaf through our memories.
Travelling for me it's to discover new places, facing new challenges, falling in love with new things, feeling new emotions and in a certain way being new each time.

#millo #milloland #helsingborg #helsingbordcentralstation #mural #murales

‚ÄúThis is not a dream‚Äù

I realized this wall for @fabrikaffiti Urban Art Festival 2018 in Tbilisi, Georgia.
The main feeling of my staying has been how strong could be fighting to realize your dream. 
Georgia is a unique country with a very ancient history and a more hard recent one, Tblisi the capital, where I 've been, can be considered, for example, a mix of all these different pieces.
The whole nation seemed to me in bloom and the people is starting to dream bigger.

From each root it's possible to grow up a beautiful tree.

#millo #milloland #thisisnotadream #tbilisi #tiflis #georgia #fabrikaffiti #fabrikaffiti2018 #fabrika #mural #muralart

‚ÄúWeave‚Äù
I painted this mural for @mistakermaker during @estau_estarrejaarteurbana in Estarreja, a small city in the northern part of Portugal. It's known for the presence of waterways where the colored "moliceiros" sail in order to fish and commerce.
Moreover the handmade fabric is the most known artisanal product in the city and for this reason the traditional ‚Äúloom‚Äù is the symbol of this artistic espression.
We should remember our roots to weave our path.
